scene.message:
Maki: That mask is cute! I'd{nl}
love to decorate my room{nl}
with it.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: {ctl0f:1}, don't let{nl}
yourself be fooled into{nl}
buying something dubious.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: These days, I find{nl}
myself wondering about those{nl}
two's relationship...{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: So Pretty! This is one{nl}
of those Japanese good-luck{nl}
figurines, isn't it?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Is this a dog? A{nl}
beckoning dog? Something seems{nl}
off...{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: If the shopkeeper's{nl}
shady, even the figurines{nl}
look shady.{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: Demons have{nl}
increased lately. But they{nl}
feel different from the ones{nl}
that girl in black brought.{waitkey}{ret}

Tsurunkamen: Ho ho ho ho...{nl}
Well come, indeed. What sort{nl}
of wares do you require?{waitkey}{ret}

Kamentsurun: Ho ho ho ho...{nl}
Gemstones I love above all{nl}
else.{waitkey}{clearbox}I'm running a blowout trade —{nl}
your gems for my treasured{nl}
wares.{waitkey}Care to give it a try?{waitkey}{ret}
